      <description>If we agree that lines have no curvature and circles have constant curvature then we&amp;rsquo;re more or less forced to say that curvature of a circle should be inversely proportional to the radius, after all a line is a circle with an infinite radius. We might as well
 Define the curvature \(\kappa\)    at every point of a circle of radius \(r\)    to be \(1/r\)   .</description>
